<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by greywolffe:
[B]My 2¢ worth on this one.

This whole NBG thing puzzles me somewhat.  Growing up my cleric, I have not experienced this mode of thinking until after hitting level 50.  I'm all in favor of getting a piece of equipment by default but would be just as thrilled if it was rolled for by everyone.  EVEN if I loose.
Everyone can and does benifit from every non-no drop item in the game.  Just because I can't weild a lammy does not mean I cannot benefit from the SALE of it.  
Regeants cost us clerics a fortune and any monies I can recoup via the sale of an item benefit me more than the warrior getting it by default.  AND I believe that same goes for the warrior that cannot use the Donal's pieces that drop but CAN benefit from the sale/trade of that item.
I'm always playing the pickup groups I'm with by ear nowadays.  If they want to default items to a specific class then that's ok, if they want to FFA then that's fine with me as well.  As long as the group agrees as a whole everyone has fun and gets something good.
Guess to me NBG or FFA makes no difference to me.  Either will eventually get me what I want one way or another.
[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
