 exe, cav, and sav.  And twice came walked past into sage room while we were sitting there and killed the scribe PH, so his arguement didn't hold much water.<P>Kaharz Stronginthearm <BR>46th lvl cleric of Brell<BR>Rodcet Nife<BR>Flames of Faradhim<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Brambodius</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sure fire way to stay cool with your group.<P>1) When you are in an area that drops your equip make sure that either the classes that aren't up for uber NBG drops are getting priority on other junk (bonus to rolls or whatever).  This is especially important to chanters who IMHO work their asses off and get screwed big time by NBG.<P>2) When you are in an area that doesn't drop your junk, promote NBG.  Its hard for people to argue with a non-dropping class that is promoting NBG and its the better loot policy anyways.  Consider suggesting some way to handle the non-class loot if you can to get some equalization going.<P>You may spend some time chatting about loot in the group while you are breaking in but a good group won't mind the discussion if it keeps the group togethor and everyone happy.<P>Brambodius - Temple of Bristlebane<BR>Quellious</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Badaf</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aladain: "I'm just expressing frustration how its somehow reguarded fair that when a group breaks up, it "resets" the random rules, thus allowing the same people to win the same item multiple times, at times, in front of the same people they won that item in the first place. Warrior01 wins Item01 that Cleric01 can use. Group breaks up, 5 hours later, group reforms again with same Warrior01 and Cleric01, but rest in group are different. Same item drops. Warrior01 randoms because he sold the first item and can loot it again. He wins roll and gets item. Fair? No" <P>Yes its perfectly, 100% 