et items. See how this is unfair to the classes that do not have any drops in that area? NBG would be more fair (although not as fair as randoming in my opinion) IF characters that do not have drops at that location were the ONLY ones allowed to roll on items that no one in the group could use. <P>"I've gotten several things on NBG and still have. You bet I'll sell or trade in the future, but they will get used quite a bit before that point"<P>Again whats the big deal about using an item before its traded/sold? Still this just does not make sense to me. The bottom line is that item can benifit any person in the group."<P>"Quite a difference from a warrior winning a cleric item, and 5 seconds later, /auctioning the zone."<P>So 10 seconds later he trades the item for a Lamination blade to a cleric that just won one over in the necro/guard camp. <P>15 seconds have elapsed. WOW, i can't believe that item got unused for 15 WHOLE seconds. See how this whole speel on "time used" really is irrelevent to this matter? </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">greywolffe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">My 2¢ worth on this one.<P>This whole NBG thing puzzles me somewhat.  Growing up my cleric, I have not experienced this mode of thinking until after hitting level 50.  I'm all in favor of getting a piece of equipment by default but would be just as thrilled if it was rolled for by everyone.  EVEN if I loose.<BR>Everyone can and does benifit from every non-no drop item in the game.  Just because I can't weild a lammy does not mean I cannot benefit from the SALE of it.  <BR>Regeants cost us clerics a fortune and any monies I can recoup via the sale of an item benefit me more than the warrior getting it by default.  AND I believe that same goes for the warrior that cannot use the Donal's pieces that drop but CAN benefit from the sale/trade of that item.<BR>I'm always playing the pickup groups I'm with by ear nowadays.  If they want to default items to a specific class then that's ok, if they want to FFA then that's fine with me as well.  As long as the group agrees as a whole everyone has fun and gets something good.<BR>Guess to me NBG or FFA makes no difference to me.  Either will eventually get me what I want one way or another.<P>------------------<BR>Greywolffe Silverstarr<BR>52nd Cleric of Tunare<BR>E'Marr<p>[This message has been edited by greywolffe (edited 04-16-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Corynthia</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">there is one place in Norrath that me avoids, and that is LGUK, that is breeding place for greedy people, at me server atleast.<BR>me has only had good experience groupin with people in Karnor, the loot has been terrible for me there hehehe  the /random commands hates me  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"> but me dont care really.<BR>and about sebilis, well me only go there with people me know and trust, had one very bad xp there about greed and that almost cost me corpse.  we were campin 4 doors, and also takin blood.  then the ranger in our group says that emperor is up, and our rogue says that we can take him out easily(average lvl was 54 on groupmates) so we go and pull the 4 guards, but the enchanter cant mezz them and we are wiped out.  oh well, me learned from that hehe.<P>------------------<BR>Corynthia-Dominion of Unity<BR>50 proof dwarven cleric<BR>Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
